Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.72,0:00:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.23,0:00:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Rage!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.48,0:00:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(611,542)}Hey, get a hold of yourself, Kaito! Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.41,0:00:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,550)}Kaito!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.03,0:00:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,540)}Faker-{\i1}sama{\i0}... Dr. Faker-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.53,0:00:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito... {\i1}That{\i0} Kaito has lost to Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.62,0:00:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all that happened, shouldn't we terminate the tournament...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.46,0:00:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should we terminate it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything goes as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.07,0:00:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we still have the Sphere Field to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.77,0:00:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Finals will continue as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.83,0:00:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As-As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.61,0:00:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito... has lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.56,0:00:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito's... Kaito's soul is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron took it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing Kaito wanted... was to save Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.76,0:01:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He only wanted to protect what's precious to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.94,0:01:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron used the power of the crest to take away the souls of Droite, Kaito, and Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.72,0:01:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he is defeated in a Duel...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.98,0:01:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that power were to be destroyed, then perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.13,0:01:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'll do that! I'm gonna kick his butt for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.09,0:01:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.56,0:01:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!\NGuys...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.99,0:01:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck to you, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.94,0:01:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got high hopes for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.03,0:01:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.31,0:01:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the power of my 'Bring it to 'Em'!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better get the championship{\i1}~meow{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.67,0:01:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, you're representing us as a Duelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.15,0:01:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you let yourself be defeated by that Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.31,0:01:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Yuma, you as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!\N Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.46,0:01:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.74,0:02:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, thank you. I'm gonna win the championship for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.71,0:02:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With everyone's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.78,0:02:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, a Duel Lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.78,0:02:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kotori!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat it and be sure to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.69,0:02:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.71,0:02:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better promise me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely positive!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.75,0:02:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd still go even if I stopped him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.83,0:02:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.17,0:03:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.07,0:03:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, what scenery do you suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}awaits us on the other side of this hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.66,0:03:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, my friends, let's climb it together
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.83,0:03:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's too soon for us to turn back now
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.09,0:03:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The time has come to combine\N together the power dwelling inside me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta release my Soul Drive
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Advance, advance, beyond the limits of your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come along with me and burn our flame of life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:04:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep running, keep running, until you get there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once again, once again, keep those challenges coming
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My friends, keep on living in the here and now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep pressing onward together no matter what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like there is only one sun in the sky, this shining glory is just as unique!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.78,0:04:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who dared to stand in their way was deemed a foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.47,0:04:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many a battle did they fight, including the survival-death matches,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(589,490)}"Number 65: An All-Out Battle Between Numbers! Yuma vs Tron!\N The Surprising Duel in the Ultra Different Dimension!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.09,0:04:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}during the first part of the World Duel Carnivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,520)\i1}They defeated enemy after enemy to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,520)\i1}Whom will shine the sun on their dash to immense glory?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,520)}These two have survived this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.22,0:05:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I give you the Dark Horse of the tournament, the Duelist with the mysterious mask, Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Against the miraculous wonder boy, Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.32,0:05:10.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Final of the century!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.57,0:05:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the stage now will be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.31,0:05:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Made by Heartland's top advanced technology:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.08,0:05:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Sphere Field!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.60,0:05:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Sphere Field is a far cry from any of the fields you've fought on up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.85,0:05:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is simulated space from the Parallel Worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron, Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.63,0:05:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use all the Numbers you have to your heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of the outcome, you both will...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha... What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.41,0:06:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Sphere Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.84,0:06:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that Faker managed to complete it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Sphere Field, take our two best Duelists...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.41,0:06:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...to the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.83,0:06:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal with that field?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.60,0:06:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, that means this special field is built by a mysterious energy from a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.96,0:06:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job making it this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.90,0:06:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was wandering the threshold between the Parallel World in a living Hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.57,0:06:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave up on life countless times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.62,0:06:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In those moments, I recalled the memory of your father, Kazuma, who gave me constant support.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.81,0:07:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to say this quite often:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Friends, companions, and a heart that will never give up."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after being betrayed by Faker, I came to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.81,0:07:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His talk about friends and comrades...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...all became completely meaningless to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have to admit that the part about, "a heart that will never give up" is quite important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because I never gave up that I had the hope to get my revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.44,0:07:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was able to be reborn in this form!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.83,0:07:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not right! And I promised III!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.46,0:07:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me: "Please save my family!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron, this is why I'll fight for III with everything I've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To {\i1}save{\i0} me? From {\i1}what{\i0}, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.89,0:07:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that obvious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.67,0:07:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will drive out the demon of revenge inside you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.72,0:08:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For your revenge, you sacrificed III, V, and IV!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.53,0:08:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, those kids haven't been very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.65,0:08:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As punishment, they are now lying side by side as three hollow shells without souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hollow shells?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.73,0:08:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. The crest I gave the three of them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.32,0:08:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,granted them power, but as a price, it was directly linked to their souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers require a huge amount of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If such a Duel is lost, the soul will be consumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.54,0:08:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The result is quite obvious, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... knew that this would happen...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.05,0:08:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can a human with such an evil heart truly exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.46,0:08:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself their parent!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.09,0:08:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They already knew about your emptiness of revenge, but you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the bond between parent and child?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, {\i1}Faker{\i0} is the one to blame for all this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't you get revenge against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.11,0:08:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Faker did take Kazuma away from you, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:09:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Dad... My dad would never want me to take revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.59,0:09:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Kazuma really thinks that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, couldn't it be that he already started his revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.33,0:09:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Astral?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.66,0:09:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.66,0:09:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A terrible power is dwelling in the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They could destroy this world with their enormous force, couldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.91,0:09:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, aren't you the messenger lending him power to take revenge on this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuma did send Astral to this world, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.10,0:09:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't... Astral is the messenger to take revenge on this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.46,0:09:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you collecting this terrible power as well, Faker!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- What the?\N - Who's that old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.40,0:09:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}- He's kinda scary!\N - Is he about to do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.35,0:09:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Dr. Faker?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.88,0:10:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Long time no see, Byron.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.29,0:10:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your rejuvenation took me by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.57,0:10:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go pay you a visit in due time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.61,0:10:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I take all of Yuma's Numbers, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop joking around here! Dr. Faker! Tron!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.73,0:10:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of you no-good adults once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.96,0:10:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now {\i0}that{\i1} sounds interesting. I'm looking {\i1}forward{\i0} to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you! We're gonna win this, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.59,0:10:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, for everyone here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.89,0:10:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}allow me to explain the Dueling rules of the Sphere Field!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This field has been developed to maximize the power of the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Each player can overlay two Monsters of the same level in his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.39,0:10:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}then, ignoring the Summoning conditions, a random Numbers Monster will be Special Summoned from the Extra Deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.69,0:11:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But a Number that has been Summoned in that way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.78,0:11:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}will be destroyed once its Overlay Units are used up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.42,0:11:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, use this as best as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.74,0:11:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Duelists chosen by the Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.23,0:11:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Heart Burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.68,0:11:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will start! My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.20,0:11:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use the effect of the field right from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take 2 Level Four Monsters from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.22,0:11:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay Heraldic Beasts Aberconway and Yale!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.03,0:11:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a Number coming already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.98,0:11:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it's a Number I can't choose myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.22,0:11:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Special Summon Number 56,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.76,0:11:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goldrat in Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.59,0:12:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,600 Defense Points? A Number this weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.50,0:12:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.04,0:12:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.59,0:12:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think the Numbers really have the power to destroy the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.94,0:12:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.64,0:12:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're still thinking about what Tron said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.57,0:12:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.08,0:12:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have I really been sent to this world for revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.28,0:12:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a clue why you've been sent to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.95,0:12:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I've come to know more than anyone that you're not a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the Numbers really have that crazy sort of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.70,0:12:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these guys should never get a hold of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral, I'll hand them to you because I know you'll do the right thing with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.18,0:12:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.37,0:13:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best to defeat this Tron.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.53,0:13:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.73,0:13:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we surprise him with some secret strategy you've been saving up 'til now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.73,0:13:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.53,0:13:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't rely on me anymore today!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, about strategy and your Dueling style...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.45,0:13:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're back to our usual way now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.52,0:13:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's there! I'll bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.12,0:13:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I Overlay the Level Four Gagaga Magician and Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.37,0:13:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Number I Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.73,0:13:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 12!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Armor Ninja Crimson Shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.81,0:14:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, with his Attack Power, he can defeat Goldrat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.73,0:14:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Force yourself through!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crimson Shadow, attack Goldrat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crimson Slash of Moon Shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.79,0:14:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.74,0:14:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.72,0:14:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nice work, Yuma, Astral... That's the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Bring forth more of your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The more power you bring forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.67,0:14:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...the tighter you grasp your own necks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.42,0:14:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take two Level Four Monsters from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.40,0:14:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay Heraldic Beasts Twin Head Eagle and Aberconway!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.59,0:15:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 10!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.81,0:15:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining White Knight Illuminator!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.57,0:15:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tha... That's... Kaito's Number.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? So Kaito used this, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's useful for {\i1}something{\i0} after {\i1}all{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.93,0:15:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron... You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be swayed by his words!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.17,0:15:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I detach one Overlay Unit from Illuminator,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to send one card from my hand to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.64,0:15:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I draw one card from the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.40,0:15:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...activate the effect of Aberconway, who was sent to the Graveyard as an Overlay Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.35,0:15:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By Banishing Aberconway from my Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can add the other Aberconway in my Graveyard back into my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.62,0:15:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going for it again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.62,0:15:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Four Heraldic Beasts Aberconway and Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 30!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.70,0:16:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acid Golem of Destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got... two Numbers now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.65,0:16:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's still another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, this is my {\i1}special service{\i0} to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.15,0:16:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay two Heraldic Beast Unicorns!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.18,0:16:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 8!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.70,0:16:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heraldic King Genome Heriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you showed yourself, Genome Heriter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.50,0:16:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got three Numbers now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.14,0:16:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're aware, aren't you, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.87,0:16:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genome Heriter has many Monster Effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.98,0:17:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go! I'll activate Genome Heriter's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.75,0:17:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, for this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Attack Power of one battling Monster the opponent controls will become zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Crimson Shadow's Attack Power changes to zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.84,0:17:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Genome Heriter's Attack Power becomes the original Attack Power of my opponent's Monster it battles!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, the Attack Power didn't change at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.02,0:17:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.28,0:17:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genome Heriter, give the death blow to Crimson Shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.85,0:17:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just use Crimson Shadow's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.35,0:17:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use the Trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you just answer the attack with a Monster Effect, we'll still receive damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.19,0:17:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we take consecutive attacks like this, we will...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.74,0:17:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate! Half Guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Half Guard negates destruction during this battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.73,0:17:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and after the battle, Crimson Shadow will change into Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.62,0:18:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn... he took a lot Life from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tch... So it's in Defense Mode now, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.77,0:18:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, never mind that. Go, Acid Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.07,0:18:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acid Splash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.80,0:18:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crimson Shadow's effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.43,0:18:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, Crimson Shadow will not be destroyed by this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.24,0:18:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not finished yet! Go, Illuminator!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.25,0:18:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Crimson Shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crimson Shadow's effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, he won't be destroyed by this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.47,0:19:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow I managed to block it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.77,0:19:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Really{\i0} now? Your Monster just lost all its Overlay Units.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Sphere Field's effect activates, and all Monsters Special Summoned by its effect will be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.03,0:19:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, without the Trap, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} would have lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.96,0:19:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end my turn with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.01,0:19:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tron...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.26,0:19:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't quail, Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show your 'Bring it to 'Em' to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.29,0:19:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.29,0:19:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.85,0:19:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Summon a Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! From my hand, I Overlay Tasukerton and Flelf!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:20:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 34!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.59,0:20:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer Beast Terrabyte!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.07,0:20:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Activate the Magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate Xyz Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Xyz-Treasure, for every Xyz Monster on the field, I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...draw one card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are four Numbers on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.77,0:20:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... I can draw four cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.95,0:20:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I Overlay Needle Swordsman and Amarylease!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 17!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leviath Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.39,0:21:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will Overlay Rai Rider and Zubaba Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.24,0:21:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here, here, here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.25,0:21:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.07,0:21:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now both of them have three Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.49,0:21:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma, good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.62,0:21:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, both sides have Summoned three strong Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.46,0:21:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whom will the Goddess of Victory smile upon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.41,0:21:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Heart Burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, the true fight is just starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.16,0:22:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you why you should {\i1}fear{\i0} me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.89,0:22:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite thoroughly!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I couldn't ask for more! Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.58,0:22:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.97,0:22:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Move on ahead, speeding up our throbbing beats
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.98,0:22:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Listen boys and girls, here's the secret to boys and girls like you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.44,0:22:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're really just so spontaneous, wild as can be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.32,0:22:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I bet you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You might be a handful, but what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.45,0:22:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be up to no good, but learn for real
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.08,0:22:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go the unpredictable route and shuffle your cards with a goal in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.33,0:23:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whenever you feel like you've lost your way, just take a minute to close your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.59,0:23:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shout "stop!" with all you've got, and there's your boundary line.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.47,0:23:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We stand tall, until we have victory in our grasp
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.77,0:23:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just stop here, not when we don't want to have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.27,0:23:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if we get hurt, we can't just hesitate now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.57,0:23:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We won't just give up, not when our future's a lot brighter than our today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.95,0:23:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seriousness... It'll only make us keep fighting even harder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.41,0:23:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll always get as fascinated as we want, and we'll fight on every day
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.28,0:23:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With our respective Numbers, Tron and I clash hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.00,0:23:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During this showdown, Tron's trump has finally showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.24,0:24:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at least, that guy's mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.65,0:24:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that Number have any weakness at all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone believes you will return to normal one day!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, use the ZeXaL Weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.99,0:24:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ever give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.47,0:24:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.34,0:24:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Terrifying Duel! Arise, Hero of Bond ZEXAL!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.70,0:24:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's your true face?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.18,0:24:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally the fight of Numbers has started!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.10,0:24:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of fantastic Numbers will appear! It's so exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.74,0:24:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.50,0:24:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that tonight's dinner is a Number?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.94,0:24:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I think you mean {\i1}nanban zuke{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.94,0:24:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}TL: Nanban zuke = vegetables pickled in Chayenne-Pepper{\i0}
